# Cheatsheet filter / collapse interaction.
#
# Spec ambiguity (the actual bug): collapsed sections are special-
# cased in `visible_sections()` to return empty rows, BUT that
# branch runs BEFORE the filter narrowing. So if a user collapses
# a section then types `/save`, that collapsed section is STILL
# rendered as a `(collapsed)` header — even if it doesn't contain
# any matching rows.
#
# The user-visible bug: it looks like more sections match than
# actually do, AND a row matching the query that's inside a
# collapsed section is hidden with no hint that it exists.

write hello.rs "fn main() {}"
open hello.rs

command view.cheatsheet
expect screen contains "Cheatsheet"

# Collapse all so we have a known-collapsed state.
key Z

# Filter for something that DEFINITELY won't match any group name —
# but if filtered correctly, all `(collapsed)` headers should
# disappear (since there are no matching rows underneath).
key /
type ZZZNEVERMATCHESZZZ

# BUG: collapsed headers still render even though the filter has
# zero matches. We expect to see "no matches" in a correct world.
# Run shows the bug — the screen still shows collapsed section
# headers, so "no matches" is NOT shown.
expect screen contains "(collapsed)"
